com.xilinx.rapidwright.device

Class Site

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.Site
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PBlockCorner, Serializable

    public class Site
extends Object
implements Serializable, PBlockCorner
    This class represents a site, a logic hierarchy level that is below a tile and generally contains one or more BELs. A common example of a site is a SLICE.
    See Also:

      • hasPin

        public boolean hasPin(String pinName)
        Checks if the site pin exists on this site.

        Vivado Tcl:

        [get_site_pins -of [get_sites $site] -filter NAME==$site/$pinName] != ""

        Parameters:
        pinName - Name of the site pin to check.
        Returns:
        True if this site has the named site pin, false otherwise.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • isCompatibleSiteType

        public boolean isCompatibleSiteType(SiteTypeEnum otherType)
        This method will check if the SiteTypeEnum otherType can be placed at this primitive site. Most often only if they are equal can this be true. However there are a few special cases that require extra handling. For example a SLICEL can reside in a SLICEM site but not vice versa.
        Parameters:
        otherType - The primitive type to try to place on this site.
        Returns:
        True if otherType can be placed at this primitive site, false otherwise.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • getNeighborSite

        public Site getNeighborSite(int dx,
                            int dy)
        This will attempt to locate a neighbor site of similar type (pblock-compatible) with the provided X,Y offset. For example, if this method was called on the site SLICE_X2Y2.getNeighborSite(-1,3), it should return the site SLICE_X1Y5, if it exists in the device.
        Parameters:
        dx - The X offset of the desired neighbor site.
        dy - The Y offset of the desired neighbor site.
        Returns:
        The neighbor site at the specified offset, or null if it couldn't be found.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • getCorrespondingSite

        public Site getCorrespondingSite(SiteTypeEnum type,
                                 Tile newSiteTile)
        A method to get the corresponding primitive site for current in a different tile. For example in a Virtex 7, there are 2 slices in a CLB tile, when moving a module the current slice must go in the same spot in a new CLB tile
        Parameters:
        current - The current primitive site of the instance.
        newSiteTile - The tile of the new proposed site.
        Returns:
        The corresponding site in tile newSite, or null if no corresponding site exists.
        Since:
        2018.2.0
